## Filter Chain

### Downmix

Stereo-to-mono downmix using FFmpeg's standard downmix matrix.

### Rumble high-pass

Removes subsonic rumble before the gate. Fixed corner, 2-pole Butterworth (12 dB/oct), non-adaptive.

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Frequency (Hz) | 80 |
| Poles | 2 |
| Width (Q) | 0.707 |
| Mix | 1.00 |
| Transform | tdii |

### Band-limit low-pass

Unconditional 20.5 kHz band-limit (2-pole, 12 dB/oct), giving the encoder a consistent bandwidth. Non-adaptive.

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Frequency (Hz) | 20500 |
| Poles | 2 |
| Width (Q) | 0.707 |
| Mix | 1.00 |
| Transform | tdii |

### Noise removal

anlmdn Non-Local Means denoiser at the source rate, followed by an afftdn FFT spectral denoise tail.

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Strength (s) | 1.00e-05 |
| Patch (s) | 0.0060 |
| Research (s) | 0.0020 |
| Smooth (m) | 3 |
| afftdn enabled | yes |
| afftdn noise reduction (dB) | 12 |
| afftdn noise type | w |
| afftdn track noise | yes |

### Speech gate

Soft expander for inter-speech cleanup. Threshold and range are adapted per file; the threshold and range values below are in dB.

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Threshold (dB) | -67.67 |
| Ratio | 1.5 |
| Attack (ms) | 5 |
| Release (ms) | 375 |
| Range (dB) | -22.00 |
| Knee | 3.0 |
| Makeup | 1.0 |
| Detection | rms |

### Levelling compressor

Gentle levelling. Threshold is speech-RMS-relative (adapted per file); ratio, attack, release, knee are fixed.

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Threshold (dB) | -36.38 |
| Ratio | 3.0 |
| Attack (ms) | 10 |
| Release (ms) | 200 |
| Makeup (dB) | 0.0 |
| Knee | 4.0 |
| Mix | 1.00 |

### De-esser

Sibilance reduction. Intensity is adapted from the speech-region sibilant-band excess; amount and frequency are fixed (FFmpeg deesser 0-1 normalised params).

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Enabled | yes |
| Intensity (i) | 0.00 |
| Amount (m) | 0.50 |
| Frequency (f) | 0.80 |

